  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: Unread messages counter badge doesn't fit large numbers on chat list screen.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nios: number is inside the badge\r\nandroid: number is not cut off\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nios: Number is outside the badge\r\nandroid: number cut off (maximum 3 symbols shown)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n#### ios\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Have chat with more than 300+ unread messages (join #status public channel for example)\r\n- Go to chat list\r\n- Number is out of badge container\r\n\r\n#### android\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Have chat with 1234 (any 4-digit number) unread messages (join #status public channel for example)\r\n- Go to chat list\r\n- You will see \"123\" unread counter, not \"1234\"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Android or iOS.)\r\nOperating System: iOS (simulator) and Android (simulator)\r\n\r\n<img width=\"528\" alt=\"screenshot 2018-01-04 11 46 11\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23836/34556324-e705e6b0-f146-11e7-9e4d-0a95906463fd.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"555\" alt=\"screenshot 2018-01-04 13 30 23\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/23836/34559620-918d661a-f153-11e7-98ac-f0e4f7b44766.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  ",
